GitHub Workflow Guide
1. Branch Naming Convention
All branches must follow this naming pattern:

Team	Feature Branch	Fix Branch
Backend	feature/be-&lt;description&gt;	fix/be-&lt;description&gt;
Frontend	feature/fe-&lt;description&gt;	fix/fe-&lt;description&gt;
Cross-Platform	feature/cross-&lt;description&gt;	fix/cross-&lt;description&gt;
DevOps	feature/devops-&lt;description&gt;	fix/devops-&lt;description&gt;
Testing	feature/test-&lt;description&gt;	fix/test-&lt;description&gt;
Examples:
feature/be-user-authentication
feature/fe-login-page
fix/be-database-connection
fix/fe-button-styling
feature/cross-offline-mode
fix/cross-api-sync
❌ Invalid branch names:
user-auth (missing prefix)
feature-backend-login (wrong format)
fix/login (missing team code)
new-feature (missing prefix and team)


