### Detailed Steps:

#### Step 1: Create Branch
```bash
# Make sure you're on main and it's up to date
git checkout main
git pull origin main

# Create your feature/fix branch
git checkout -b feature/be-user-login
Step 2: Make Changes & Commit
bash
Copy
# Make your changes
git add .
git commit -m "feat(be): add user login endpoint"
Step 3: Push Branch
bash
Copy
git push -u origin feature/be-user-login
Step 4: Open Pull Request
Go to GitHub repository
Click the yellow banner "Compare & pull request"
Fill in PR template:
Title: Brief description (e.g., "Add user authentication")
Description: What changed, why, and testing done
Assign 1 sub-team leader as reviewer
Click "Create pull request"
Step 5: Code Review
Sub-team leader reviews code
Address any feedback with new commits
Re-request review after changes
Step 6: CI Checks
Automated checks run on every push
All checks must pass before merging
Fix any failing checks
Step 7: Merge
Click "Squash and merge" button
Delete branch after merging
Step 8: Cleanup
bash
Copy
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git branch -d feature/be-user-login        # Delete local
git push origin --delete feature/be-user-login  # Delete remote
3. Commit Message Format
All commits must follow Conventional Commits format:
plain
Copy
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

[optional body]

[optional footer]
Types:
Table
Type	Use When
feat	New feature
fix	Bug fix
docs	Documentation only changes
style	Code style changes (formatting, semicolons, etc)
refactor	Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
test	Adding or correcting tests
chore	Build process, dependencies, or auxiliary tool changes
Scopes:
Table
Scope	Team
be	Backend
fe	Frontend
cross	Cross-Platform/Mobile
devops	DevOps/Infrastructure
test	Testing
Examples:
bash
Copy
# Feature commits
feat(be): add JWT authentication middleware
feat(fe): create login page component
feat(cross): implement offline sync

# Fix commits
fix(be): resolve database connection timeout
fix(fe): correct button alignment on mobile
fix(cross): fix audio player crash

# Other commits
docs: update API documentation
test(be): add unit tests for user service
chore(devops): setup GitHub Actions workflow
style(fe): format CSS files
refactor(be): simplify user query logic
❌ Invalid commit messages:
updated stuff (no type/scope)
fix (no subject)
feature login (wrong format)
Added new feature (past tense, no type/scope)
4. Branch Protection Rules
The main branch is protected with these rules:
Table
Rule	Status
❌ No direct pushes to main	Enforced
✅ All changes via Pull Request	Required
👥 At least 1 sub-team leader approval	Required
✓ CI checks must pass	Required
🔄 Branch must be up to date	Required
🛡️ Applies to administrators	Yes
5. Quick Command Reference
bash
Copy
# Start new work
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git checkout -b feature/be-<description>

# Daily workflow
git add .
git commit -m "type(scope): description"
git push origin feature/be-<description>

# Update branch with latest main
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git checkout feature/be-<description>
git rebase main
git push -f origin feature/be-<description>

# After PR is merged
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git branch -d feature/be-<description>
git push origin --delete feature/be-<description>
